From 22fc6b2d96d34e030b9820241515c5e6d6878062 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: David Gornshtein <davidgornshtein@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 3 May 2026 13:46:31 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] [Python] add mx.from_dlpack(obj) Metal-aware consumer
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Adds a top-level mx.from_dlpack(obj) that consumes either a raw
PyCapsule (named "dltensor" or "dltensor_versioned") or any object
whose __dlpack__() chain yields one. The consumer dispatches on
DLDevice.device_type:

- kDLCPU (1): copy into a fresh MLX allocation; producer's deleter
  runs immediately after the copy.
- kDLMetal (8): wrap the foreign MTLBuffer as an mx.array via
  array(allocator::Buffer, Shape, Dtype, Deleter) (the constructor
  MLX already exposes for foreign buffers). Storage mode validated to
  be MTLResourceStorageModeShared; non-Shared rejected with a clear
  error message that tells the producer how to fix its allocator.

Other device types (kDLCUDA, kDLROCM, ...) rejected explicitly. Used
capsules detected and rejected on second consume. Non-contiguous
strided views rejected.

Motivation: enable zero-copy DLPack interop with TVM-NDArray (which
allocates Metal buffers as Shared via TVM_METAL_STORAGE_MODE=shared,
the paired apache/tvm patch), mlx-mfa, and similar Apple Silicon
producers. Today MLX advertises kDLMetal in __dlpack_device__() but
exports kDLCPU capsules and offers no consumer at all, so cross-stack
DLPack interop on Apple Silicon is one-way and host-mediated.

Implementation:
- dlpack_consumer.{h,cpp} — entry point, capsule parsing, CPU path,
  used-capsule detection, deleter wiring.
- dlpack_consumer_metal.cpp — Metal-only TU compiled when
  MLX_BUILD_METAL=ON; handles kDLMetal capsules.
- dlpack_consumer_no_metal.cpp — stub linked otherwise.
- dlpack_format.h — local DLPack ABI structs (DLManagedTensor +
  DLManagedTensorVersioned + kDL device codes); not vendoring upstream
  dlpack.h to avoid a third-party dep churn for an MVP.
- array.cpp — m.def("from_dlpack", ...).
- CMakeLists.txt — new sources via $<IF:$<BOOL:${MLX_BUILD_METAL}>...>.

Tests: python/tests/test_dlpack_consumer.py covers existence,
NumPy round-trip, raw capsule round-trip, self round-trip (currently
exercises CPU path because MLX export still emits kDLCPU — Phase 2),
13 dtype variants, non-DLPack rejection, used-capsule rejection,
strided rejection. 8/8 pass.

Phase 2 (separate PR): fix MLX's exporter (convert.cpp lines 100-159)
to actually emit kDLMetal capsules when running on Metal — currently
__dlpack_device__() and the produced capsule disagree.
